2 dead, 4 arrested after Florida crime spree
HAINES CITY, Fla. (AP) â€” Authorities have arrested a fourth man suspected in a crime spree involving a pawn shop robbery and the fatal shootings of two women in their central Florida home.
The Polk County Sheriff's Office says in a news release that Terrell Williams was arrested Friday morning in Haines City.
Williams and three others face multiple charges.
Seventy-two year-old Patricia Moran and her 51-year-old daughter, Deborah Royal, were found dead in their home early Friday.
Deputies say the quartet robbed an Auburndale pawn shop earlier.